      "message": "previously any time you did `logging.Get(c)` it just bound c to a struct, but every log line would actually still do lookups in c ... #faceplam.\n\nTechnically this does two lookups in c (level and fields), but now only does them once in the case that you\u0027ve used `logging.Get` instead of e.g. logging.Infof(c, ...).\n\nThe other way I could do this would be to cache the lookups in loggerImpl, which would mean logging.Debugf(context_at_Info, ...) would still only do one lookup (and cache it somewhere which gets tossed). \n\nMy feeling is that if you care about speed/allocations, you are using logging.Get to amortize the cost of this stuff anyway.\n\nwdyt?",
